3.6.9 — Disruption Resolution State Machine
This is the formalized sequence of states a traveler moves through from the moment a disruption is suspected to the moment an outcome is recorded. It sits between the Incident OS (Section 3.1) and the Trip Maturity States (Section 3.5). It is the traveler-facing resolution journey — distinct from the platform's administrative state machines.

RELATIONSHIP TO INCIDENT OS
Section 3.1 (Incident OS) defines the operational lifecycle of the Incident object. This state machine defines the traveler's resolution journey — the experiential path, not the data object states. They run in parallel and inform each other but are not the same machine.

