3.6.9.B — Filing Deadline Tracking
Filing deadlines are surfaced at ROUTING_DETERMINED and remain visible through RIGHTS_WINDOW_ACTIVE and CLAIM_ACTIVE. The platform tracks them per claim path and surfaces urgency indicators:

Days Until Deadline	Display Behavior
More than 30 days	Deadline shown as informational. No urgency indicator.
15–30 days	Deadline shown with mild indicator: "File within [X] days to preserve this option."
7–14 days	Deadline shown with clear indicator: "[X] days remaining. This window closes [date]."
Under 7 days	Deadline shown with high urgency: "[X] days left. File as soon as possible."
Deadline passed	Show as closed: "This filing window has passed. This coverage path is no longer available." — never show as an error or failure, just as information.

3.6.9.C — Parallel Track Rule
Evidence capture runs in parallel with every state. It does not wait for the traveler to decide which state they are in. From the moment DISRUPTION_CONFIRMED is reached, the evidence capture checklist is active and surfaced alongside whatever the traveler is currently doing. This is the 'never waste a moment' doctrine from the narrative Q&A session.

